<TITLE> M Saifur Rahman killed in road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 5 (bdnews24.com)Veteran BNP leader M Saifur Rahman, who was Bangladesh's longest-serving finance minister, died at Brahmanbaria Sadar Hospital following a road accident on Saturday, his personal aide said. Rahman, aged 77, was critically injured after his car's brakes failed on the Dhaka-Sylhet highway and the vehicle crashed into a roadside ditch, his personal assistant Shamsul Haque told bdnews24.com. He was rushed to the Sadar Hospital, where he was declared dead at around 3.00pm, doctors told bdnews24.com. Rahman, was on his way to Dhaka from his district town Moulavi Bazar. He went to Sylhet on Friday and offered prayers at Hajrat Shahjalal's shrine, said Haque. bdn
